Sit down.

854
00:29:42,150 --> 00:29:43,340
Calm down, calm down.

855
00:29:43,370 --> 00:29:43,880
Come on.

856
00:29:45,350 --> 00:29:46,780
Don't bother with people like that.

857
00:29:47,450 --> 00:29:48,260
Just calm down.

858
00:29:51,670 --> 00:29:53,290
What kind of person is he?

859
00:29:55,790 --> 00:30:03,260
[Heaven rewards the diligent]

860
00:29:55,870 --> 00:29:57,120
Drink less.

861
00:29:57,150 --> 00:29:58,520
Drinking too much is bad for your liver.

862
00:30:01,960 --> 00:30:03,450
Drinking harms the liver,

863
00:30:03,470 --> 00:30:04,550
but if I don't drink, my heart hurts.

864
00:30:06,780 --> 00:30:08,520
Isn't it just a project grant?

865
00:30:08,570 --> 00:30:10,720
Is it really worth getting so upset over a few thousand yuan?

866
00:30:10,760 --> 00:30:12,390
It's not about the money at all.

867
00:30:12,430 --> 00:30:13,950
This is about dignity!

868
00:30:15,130 --> 00:30:16,750
You wouldn't understand even if I explained it to you.

869
00:30:20,990 --> 00:30:22,030
We're both writers.

870
00:30:22,580 --> 00:30:24,540
Why does he get the project grant?

871
00:30:25,440 --> 00:30:27,050
Isn't it just because he has a well-connected wife?

872
00:30:28,320 --> 00:30:29,240
District chief.

873
00:30:29,240 --> 00:30:30,270
The head of a district.

874
00:30:31,060 --> 00:30:32,070
She dares to abuse power for personal gain

875
00:30:32,070 --> 00:30:33,350
and seek benefits for her family members.

876
00:30:33,800 --> 00:30:35,650
Doesn't she fear divine retribution?

877
00:30:36,120 --> 00:30:37,940
You shouldn't say such things carelessly.

878
00:30:38,230 --> 00:30:39,700
Mind your words to accumulate virtue.

879
00:30:39,780 --> 00:30:40,790
They don't even accumulate virtue.

880
00:30:40,790 --> 00:30:42,790
Why should I be the one to watch my words?

881
00:30:42,790 --> 00:30:44,070
Do you know how much effort

882
00:30:44,070 --> 00:30:45,720
I've poured into the topic of Su Xiaomei?

883
00:30:45,750 --> 00:30:48,550
Do you know how many trips I made to the library?

884
00:30:48,580 --> 00:30:49,860
To put it bluntly,

885
00:30:49,880 --> 00:30:51,200
even if I don't deserve credit,

886
00:30:51,230 --> 00:30:52,830
I should at least get credit for my hard work, right?

887
00:30:52,950 --> 00:30:54,060
Yes.

888
00:30:55,620 --> 00:30:56,840
Ouch, ouch, ouch.

889
00:30:57,470 --> 00:30:59,660
If it hurts, then stop talking so much.

890
00:31:00,070 --> 00:31:01,460
It's not such a big deal.

891
00:31:01,670 --> 00:31:02,960
It's not a big deal?

892
00:31:03,150 --> 00:31:04,720
Isn't this a big deal?

893
00:31:04,750 --> 00:31:06,370
What would you call a big deal then?

894
00:31:07,030 --> 00:31:07,800
Abusing power for personal gain.

895
00:31:07,830 --> 00:31:08,920
Swindling and plundering.

896
00:31:08,960 --> 00:31:10,150
If I don't speak up,

897
00:31:10,150 --> 00:31:11,660
I'll be bullied to death by them!

898
00:31:11,690 --> 00:31:12,450
Dad,

899
00:31:12,480 --> 00:31:13,950
could you please keep it down?

900
00:31:13,980 --> 00:31:15,690
Adults are talking. Why are you butting in, kid?

901
00:31:15,700 --> 00:31:16,500
Shut up!

902
00:31:16,530 --> 00:31:17,150
Alright.

903
00:31:17,150 --> 00:31:18,470
Why are you yelling at him?

904
00:31:18,470 --> 00:31:19,990
He didn't say anything wrong.

905
00:31:20,110 --> 00:31:21,890
And you're a graduate of a prestigious school.

906
00:31:21,920 --> 00:31:23,120
You're as petty as

907
00:31:23,150 --> 00:31:24,150
I'm petty?

908
00:31:24,180 --> 00:31:25,720
I'm petty?

909
00:31:25,940 --> 00:31:27,180
I can't even criticize him now. Is that it?

910
00:31:27,200 --> 00:31:27,550
Alright, alright.

911
00:31:27,570 --> 00:31:28,700
What do you mean "alright"?

912
00:31:29,800 --> 00:31:30,190
Mom!

913
00:31:30,190 --> 00:31:30,790
Yuling.

914
00:31:31,000 --> 00:31:32,320
Don't touch my mom!

915
00:31:32,670 --> 00:31:34,220
If you get drunk and act crazy again,

916
00:31:34,260 --> 00:31:35,740
I'll report you to your workplace for domestic violence!

917
00:31:35,760 --> 00:31:37,770
Xingchi, Xingchi.

918
00:31:37,800 --> 00:31:38,830
Don't yell at your father.

919
00:31:38,860 --> 00:31:39,920
Mom's fine.

920
00:31:40,150 --> 00:31:40,670
I'm okay.

921
00:31:40,670 --> 00:31:41,230
Can you move?

922
00:31:53,060 --> 00:31:58,550
[Midnight Eats]

923
00:31:53,110 --> 00:31:53,780
Bro.

924
00:31:55,330 --> 00:31:55,910
Lao'er.

925
00:31:55,940 --> 00:31:56,790
Come, have a seat.

926
00:31:57,400 --> 00:31:58,090
Yue'er.

927
00:31:58,120 --> 00:31:59,600
Get us another glass.

928
00:31:59,870 --> 00:32:00,470
Okay.

929
00:32:01,300 --> 00:32:01,990
You're drinking?

930
00:32:01,990 --> 00:32:03,470
Of course.

931
00:32:04,860 --> 00:32:05,460
Come on.

932
00:32:07,770 --> 00:32:09,230
I... I'll pass.

933
00:32:09,230 --> 00:32:11,090
My liver's been hurting these past couple of days.

934
00:32:11,230 --> 00:32:12,350
What do you mean your liver hurts?

935
00:32:12,510 --> 00:32:13,740
At most, you've got a fatty liver.

936
00:32:13,770 --> 00:32:14,930
It's not like you have cirrhosis.

937
00:32:14,970 --> 00:32:15,530
What's the matter?

938
00:32:15,550 --> 00:32:16,870
Getting all delicate now, are you?

939
00:32:17,330 --> 00:32:18,520
She... you know...

940
00:32:20,070 --> 00:32:21,360
You mean Yan?

941
00:32:21,550 --> 00:32:22,350
Just tell her

942
00:32:22,390 --> 00:32:23,430
that I make you drink.

943
00:32:23,460 --> 00:32:24,410
What's the problem?

944
00:32:24,800 --> 00:32:25,710
Al... alright then.

945
00:32:35,440 --> 00:32:36,270
Well...

946
00:32:36,830 --> 00:32:37,940
Have you gotten the money back?

947
00:32:41,020 --> 00:32:42,160
What should we do?

948
00:32:42,510 --> 00:32:43,620
In a couple of days,

949
00:32:44,220 --> 00:32:46,230
I won't even have money for gas.

950
00:32:54,960 --> 00:32:55,840
Cheers!

951
00:32:56,540 --> 00:32:57,350
Cheers!

952
00:33:15,600 --> 00:33:17,000
How about some stir-fried river snails?

953
00:33:18,370 --> 00:33:19,730
Ri... river snails.

954
00:33:19,800 --> 00:33:21,030
Bring us some river snails.

955
00:33:21,110 --> 00:33:21,910
Right away.

956
00:33:21,930 --> 00:33:22,930
Extra spicy, okay?

957
00:33:22,970 --> 00:33:23,330
Okay.

958
00:33:23,350 --> 00:33:24,490
Yes, yes, yes.

959
00:33:28,010 --> 00:33:29,110
Fill it up.

960
00:33:49,530 --> 00:33:50,560
You're back.

961
00:33:53,840 --> 00:33:54,720
You've been drinking again.

962
00:33:54,760 --> 00:33:55,530
Well, on my way home...

963
00:33:55,550 --> 00:33:57,420
I ran into Lao'er.

964
00:33:57,450 --> 00:33:59,430
I just took a sip.

965
00:34:00,020 --> 00:34:01,560
I'm going to bed now.

966
00:34:02,270 --> 00:34:03,200
Son,

967
00:34:03,320 --> 00:34:05,120
do you know someone called Jay Chou?

968
00:34:05,150 --> 00:34:05,750
Yes, I do.

969
00:34:05,780 --> 00:34:07,200
He's quite popular now.

970
00:34:07,220 --> 00:34:09,130
His songs are played everywhere on the streets.

971
00:34:09,670 --> 00:34:11,639
One of his songs is pretty good.

972
00:34:11,659 --> 00:34:13,739
It's called... "Listen"

973
00:34:13,770 --> 00:34:16,360
"Listen to Mom."

974
00:34:17,360 --> 00:34:18,719
Go out and learn it.

975
00:34:18,760 --> 00:34:19,790
When you've learned it, sing it for

976
00:34:20,100 --> 00:34:20,860
your mom.

977
00:34:21,080 --> 00:34:22,110
Okay, okay, okay.

978
00:34:22,139 --> 00:34:23,190
You should listen too.

979
00:34:23,210 --> 00:34:24,420
Listen to my mom

980
00:34:24,760 --> 00:34:25,760
You should drink less.

981
00:34:42,889 --> 00:34:43,900
What is this?

982
00:34:44,870 --> 00:34:46,260
I'm asking you, what is this?

983
00:35:01,860 --> 00:35:03,820
This little brat.

984
00:35:04,810 --> 00:35:05,800
You little brat.

985
00:35:05,820 --> 00:35:06,480
What are you doing?

986
00:35:06,550 --> 00:35:07,490
You're not even fully grown yet.

987
00:35:07,950 --> 00:35:09,100
What are you doing?

988
00:35:09,150 --> 00:35:10,110
Don't wrongly accuse our son.

989
00:35:10,140 --> 00:35:11,140
It's yours!

990
00:35:11,320 --> 00:35:13,160
It's from your pocket.

991
00:35:14,140 --> 00:35:15,270
No way, no way.

992
00:35:15,270 --> 00:35:17,220
I... I never use this thing.

993
00:35:18,100 --> 00:35:19,630
You... don't falsely accuse me.

994
00:35:19,670 --> 00:35:20,710
Am I falsely accusing you?

995
00:35:20,710 --> 00:35:21,840
If it's not yours, is it mine?

996
00:35:21,860 --> 00:35:23,460
Our son can testify to it.

997
00:35:23,970 --> 00:35:24,540
It's yours.

998
00:35:27,910 --> 00:35:28,990
Xie Tiancheng.

999
00:35:28,990 --> 00:35:30,620
What have you done?

1000
00:35:30,700 --> 00:35:31,140
Mom.

1001
00:35:31,140 --> 00:35:32,430
What did you do outside?

1002
00:35:33,320 --> 00:35:34,540
What have you done?

1003
00:35:34,540 --> 00:35:35,440
Stop it, Mom.

1004
00:35:35,440 --> 00:35:36,190
Get away.

1005
00:35:40,030 --> 00:35:40,750
Explain it to me clearly.

1006
00:35:40,750 --> 00:35:42,000
If you don't explain it to me clearly,

1007
00:35:42,040 --> 00:35:43,600
let's just separate!

1008
00:35:43,630 --> 00:35:44,300
Tell!

1009
00:35:44,310 --> 00:35:44,930
Whose is it?

1010
00:35:44,960 --> 00:35:46,000
Don't pinch me here. Not here!

1011
00:35:46,020 --> 00:35:47,100
Tell it!

1012
00:35:47,830 --> 00:35:48,350
No

1013
00:35:48,390 --> 00:35:49,190
Whose is it really?

1014
00:35:49,190 --> 00:35:49,750
Wait

1015
00:35:49,790 --> 00:35:50,990
If you dare lie to me, you'll see the consequences.

1016
00:35:51,030 --> 00:35:51,750
Speak!

1017
00:35:56,910 --> 00:35:57,740
Take it easy.

1018
00:35:59,370 --> 00:36:00,060
No need.

1019
00:36:00,060 --> 00:36:01,350
Just a slap.

1020
00:36:01,370 --> 00:36:02,060
It's not that bad.

1021
00:36:02,090 --> 00:36:03,760
Hurry up. The ice pack will help.

1022
00:36:07,940 --> 00:36:08,970
What happened to your face?

1023
00:36:11,030 --> 00:36:12,190
He stood up to his father

1024
00:36:12,310 --> 00:36:13,340
and got put down.

1025
00:36:13,360 --> 00:36:14,720
Here, do it yourself.

1026
00:36:18,070 --> 00:36:19,640
Did he hit your mom again?

1027
00:36:22,190 --> 00:36:23,240
My mom's back is injured.

1028
00:36:23,260 --> 00:36:24,300
It's all bruised now.

1029
00:36:25,290 --> 00:36:26,830
I don't know if she can even walk tomorrow.

1030
00:36:26,860 --> 00:36:28,070
Sometimes I really want to...

1031
00:36:28,090 --> 00:36:29,570
Don't do anything rash.

1032
00:36:30,020 --> 00:36:31,710
No matter what, he's still your father.

1033
00:36:35,590 --> 00:36:36,650
You know what?

1034
00:36:36,680 --> 00:36:37,930
In this regard,

1035
00:36:38,020 --> 00:36:39,550
my dad is a model example.

1036
00:36:40,470 --> 00:36:41,370
Listen.

1037
00:36:42,590 --> 00:36:44,070
No matter how badly he's beaten,

1038
00:36:44,110 --> 00:36:45,520
he never fights back.

1039
00:36:49,400 --> 00:36:52,170
When will this kind of life end?

1040
00:36:54,430 --> 00:36:56,140
If today is unbearable,

1041
00:36:56,430 --> 00:36:57,970
just think about tomorrow.

1042
00:36:58,980 --> 00:37:00,290
In a few years,

1043
00:37:00,440 --> 00:37:01,880
when we've all made it,

1044
00:37:01,910 --> 00:37:03,540
earning millions a year,

1045
00:37:03,910 --> 00:37:04,750
by then,

1046
00:37:04,790 --> 00:37:06,420
every family will have bought a new house.

1047
00:37:06,450 --> 00:37:07,850
At that time, when our parents gather every day,

1048
00:37:07,890 --> 00:37:09,970
they'll just play mahjong and chat about their kids.

1049
00:37:10,000 --> 00:37:11,800
Our biggest worry then

1050
00:37:11,840 --> 00:37:12,970
won't be making money,

1051
00:37:13,860 --> 00:37:15,850
but our parents being extremely bored

1052
00:37:16,260 --> 00:37:17,220
and hence

1053
00:37:17,700 --> 00:37:18,610
pressuring us to get married.

1054
00:37:20,250 --> 00:37:21,290
Just imagine that life.

1055
00:37:22,120 --> 00:37:23,190
I'm telling you,

1056
00:37:23,490 --> 00:37:25,400
Siyi definitely won't be pressured to marry.

1057
00:37:25,430 --> 00:37:26,560
She'll definitely marry early.

1058
00:37:27,230 --> 00:37:27,940
Why?

1059
00:37:28,170 --> 00:37:29,840
She's beautiful and smart,

1060
00:37:29,870 --> 00:37:30,780
and sensible too.

1061
00:37:30,810 --> 00:37:31,970
By then, she'll get into a good university.

1062
00:37:31,990 --> 00:37:33,160
I bet she'll be

1063
00:37:33,190 --> 00:37:34,650
snatched up before she even graduates.

1064
00:37:34,670 --> 00:37:35,640
That's how it was with my parents.

1065
00:37:36,260 --> 00:37:36,900
My mom

1066
00:37:36,920 --> 00:37:38,080
graduated from the Opera Academy,

1067
00:37:38,120 --> 00:37:39,290
specializing in qingyi roles.

1068
00:37:39,940 --> 00:37:41,300
The first time she performed on stage,

1069
00:37:41,320 --> 00:37:42,600
my dad spotted her.

1070
00:37:42,640 --> 00:37:44,720
At first, she really looked down on my dad.

1071
00:37:44,760 --> 00:37:45,520
But you know what?

1072
00:37:45,830 --> 00:37:47,140
On their first date,

1073
00:37:47,580 --> 00:37:49,380
my dad cooked a meal for my mom.

1074
00:37:49,440 --> 00:37:50,550
He won her over just like that.

1075
00:38:23,350 --> 00:38:24,030
Hello?

1076
00:38:24,050 --> 00:38:24,930
Linlin,

1077
00:38:24,990 --> 00:38:26,720
I watched that TV series.

1078
00:38:26,880 --> 00:38:28,250
It was so well made.

1079
00:38:28,290 --> 00:38:29,220
It was okay, right?

1080
00:38:29,240 --> 00:38:30,410
Not just okay.

1081
00:38:30,440 --> 00:38:31,690
It was excellent!

1082
00:38:31,780 --> 00:38:32,720
It didn't feel like a TV series,

1083
00:38:32,750 --> 00:38:33,940
but more like a movie.

1084
00:38:34,410 --> 00:38:35,820
That play you mentioned before

1085
00:38:35,840 --> 00:38:37,360
can I still audition for it?

1086
00:38:37,530 --> 00:38:38,510
Of course you can.

1087
00:38:39,090 --> 00:38:40,850
Then please help me get in touch with them quickly.

1088
00:38:40,870 --> 00:38:41,870
As soon as I finish shooting tomorrow,

1089
00:38:41,900 --> 00:38:43,020
I'll head to Beijing right away.

1090
00:38:43,050 --> 00:38:44,340
Wait, has your husband agreed?

1091
00:38:44,370 --> 00:38:45,840
For such a great director,

1092
00:38:45,880 --> 00:38:47,300
I have to give it a shot no matter what.

1093
00:38:47,330 --> 00:38:48,250
Don't you think so?

1094
00:38:48,310 --> 00:38:49,630
Alright, I'll ask about it.

1095
00:38:49,660 --> 00:38:50,760
Okay, okay.

1096
00:38:50,870 --> 00:38:52,350
I'll wait for your news then.

1097
00:38:52,680 --> 00:38:54,260
And about the Liu family

1098
00:38:54,710 --> 00:38:55,630
Dad, you're back.

1099
00:38:56,720 --> 00:38:57,160
Dad.

1100
00:38:57,180 --> 00:38:58,170
Have you been drinking?

1101
00:38:58,880 --> 00:39:00,420
I just had a little.

1102
00:39:00,450 --> 00:39:01,210
With whom?

1103
00:39:02,420 --> 00:39:03,540
Just by myself.

1104
00:39:05,060 --> 00:39:05,700
Well...

1105
00:39:06,050 --> 00:39:07,280
I'm going to my room.

1106
00:39:07,310 --> 00:39:09,450
It's not like Zhimei isn't coming back.

1107
00:39:14,050 --> 00:39:14,680
Dad,

1108
00:39:16,080 --> 00:39:17,270
she

1109
00:39:17,290 --> 00:39:19,420
only comes home a few days a year.

1110
00:39:19,450 --> 00:39:21,040
What's the difference between that and not coming back at all?

1111
00:39:22,210 --> 00:39:24,140
She's contributing to the family.

1112
00:39:24,170 --> 00:39:25,720
You call that a contribution?

1113
00:39:27,390 --> 00:39:28,470
Her contribution should be

1114
00:39:28,470 --> 00:39:30,880
taking care of this home for me.

1115
00:39:31,040 --> 00:39:32,870
She should be looking after Haikuo.

1116
00:39:33,610 --> 00:39:35,080
He's already in his final year of high school.

1117
00:39:36,560 --> 00:39:37,890
What are you waiting for?

1118
00:39:38,280 --> 00:39:39,270
Go study now.

1119
00:39:39,330 --> 00:39:41,040
Go take a shower quickly.

1120
00:39:52,840 --> 00:39:54,040
I really didn't lie to you.

1121
00:39:55,200 --> 00:39:57,040
I really went to collect the debt

1122
00:39:57,080 --> 00:39:58,910
from Crippled Sun.

1123
00:39:59,420 --> 00:40:01,530
That thick-skinned brute refused to pay me.

1124
00:40:01,980 --> 00:40:03,370
He tried to pawn things off to settle the debt,

1125
00:40:03,500 --> 00:40:06,110
stuffing anything he grabbed into my pockets.

1126
00:40:06,590 --> 00:40:09,840
I gave back everything to him,

1127
00:40:10,050 --> 00:40:13,530
but I didn't notice it because it was too small.

1128
00:40:15,060 --> 00:40:16,020
Don't be mad anymore, okay?

1129
00:40:17,060 --> 00:40:17,580
Alright?

1130
00:40:18,300 --> 00:40:19,230
That money

1131
00:40:19,950 --> 00:40:21,830
we won't get it back forever, right?

1132
00:40:23,320 --> 00:40:23,720
Well,

1133
00:40:23,750 --> 00:40:24,720
that's not possible.

1134
00:40:25,260 --> 00:40:26,500
I must get it back from him.

1135
00:40:26,520 --> 00:40:27,570
What can you do?

1136
00:40:30,280 --> 00:40:32,570
If he doesn't pay me back by the end of the month,

1137
00:40:32,670 --> 00:40:33,580
I'll fight him to the death.

1138
00:40:36,710 --> 00:40:38,040
Don't do anything reckless, you hear me?

1139
00:40:38,080 --> 00:40:38,770
Money is not important.

1140
00:40:38,800 --> 00:40:39,820
You can't get into trouble.

1141
00:40:40,030 --> 00:40:40,790
If something happens to you,

1142
00:40:40,810 --> 00:40:41,860
what will our son and I do?

1143
00:40:41,890 --> 00:40:42,850
Do you understand?

1144
00:40:42,870 --> 00:40:43,550
Don't worry.

1145
00:40:43,630 --> 00:40:44,500
Rest assured.

1146
00:40:44,530 --> 00:40:47,870
I won't do anything illegal, I promise.

1147
00:40:54,470 --> 00:40:55,390
Just now,

1148
00:40:56,870 --> 00:40:58,270
did I hurt you?

1149
00:40:59,420 --> 00:41:00,230
What do you think?

1150
00:41:03,670 --> 00:41:05,140
Have you practiced the Nine Yin White Bone Claw?

1151
00:41:05,170 --> 00:41:06,820
You scratched, pinched, and clawed.

1152
00:41:07,630 --> 00:41:09,590
I was just feeling anxious.

1153
00:41:09,800 --> 00:41:12,290
We haven't had any income for months.

1154
00:41:12,310 --> 00:41:15,190
We still owe several families their dividends.

1155
00:41:15,540 --> 00:41:17,410
I'm too embarrassed to face them.

1156
00:41:17,440 --> 00:41:18,360
You know,

1157
00:41:19,160 --> 00:41:20,980
if it were just our own business,

1158
00:41:21,000 --> 00:41:21,880
even if we lose money,

1159
00:41:21,920 --> 00:41:22,960
I could accept that.

1160
00:41:22,980 --> 00:41:24,180
At worst, we'll just

1161
00:41:24,220 --> 00:41:26,250
spend less.

1162
00:41:26,300 --> 00:41:27,770
We'd get through it somehow.

1163
00:41:27,790 --> 00:41:29,870
But I'm afraid of letting down our neighbors.

1164
00:41:32,330 --> 00:41:33,650
The other families are fine,

1165
00:41:33,980 --> 00:41:35,650
but considering Granny Ma's situation...

1166
00:41:40,110 --> 00:41:41,990
I feel guilty.

1167
00:41:42,890 --> 00:41:44,090
I'm really sorry.

1168
00:41:44,120 --> 00:41:46,480
We should blame that Crippled Sun.

1169
00:41:46,510 --> 00:41:48,940
He drives a Mercedes to the nightclub,

1170
00:41:48,970 --> 00:41:50,700
blowing thousands in one night,

1171
00:41:51,250 --> 00:41:52,540
but he doesn't pay back the money he owes.

1172
00:41:52,560 --> 00:41:54,370
What kind of person is that?

1173
00:42:40,240 --> 00:42:41,590
You're smart enough.

1174
00:42:42,710 --> 00:42:43,920
Why are you here?

1175
00:42:44,490 --> 00:42:46,770
I saw you leaving home earlier, and you seemed upset.

1176
00:42:46,840 --> 00:42:48,160
I was worried something might happen to you,

1177
00:42:48,190 --> 00:42:49,440
so I followed you all the way here.

1178
00:42:49,710 --> 00:42:50,870
What could possibly happen to me?

1179
00:42:54,890 --> 00:42:55,690
Let's go.

1180
00:42:56,910 --> 00:42:58,630
What are you hissing at? Come with me!
